<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-34-1337 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Atomic Energy Act of West Germany prescribes that a licence for theoperation of a nuclear power plant can only be granted if the personsresponsible for the erection, management and supervision of the operationof the plant have the required expertise. In addition, the requirementof highest possible availability of power plant also assumes that theoperating personnel are highly qualified. This qualification can onlybe attained and maintained by a long-standing objective oriented andsystematic education training. It is demonstrated how the teaching ofthe theory as a part of the education and retraining is performed inWest Germany.</TEXT></DOC>